the meaning of joie-de-vivre so that 's what joie-de-vivre means . it 's really not the point whether the anecdotes are based on real facts . it 's d.v . 's attitude , her curiosity , her passion for certain things , and her irreverence for the rest is what 's most inspiring . the writing , edited by george plimpton and christopher hemphill , is wonderfully imaginative and poetic , be it about mona lisa or buffalo bill . i recommend it to anyone with an eye for details and a passion for life